---
import BaseLayout from '~/layouts/BaseLayout.astro'

const updated = '2026-06-20'
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Grievance officer — oriz · cards"
  description="Mandatory contact under India's IT Rules 2021."
>
  <div class="spine-prose">
    <header class="page-head">
      <p class="eyebrow mono">
        <a href="/">cards</a> / <a href="/legal/">legal</a> / grievance officer
      </p>
      <h1>grievance officer</h1>
      <p class="meta">Last updated: {updated}</p>
    </header>

    <article class="prose">
      <p>
        Per the <strong>Information Technology (Intermediary Guidelines and
        Digital Media Ethics Code) Rules, 2021</strong>, the following contact
        handles complaints related to cards.oriz.in and the wider oriz family.
      </p>

      <div class="officer">
        <p><strong>Name:</strong> Chirag Singhal</p>
        <p><strong>Designation:</strong> Grievance Officer</p>
        <p><strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:whyiswhen@gmail.com">whyiswhen@gmail.com</a></p>
        <p><strong>Address:</strong> Bhubaneswar, Odisha, India 751001</p>
        <p><strong>Response time:</strong> Acknowledgement within 24 hours; resolution within 15 days.</p>
      </div>

      <h2>What you can report</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Card data on cards.oriz.in that is wrong, outdated, or misleading.</li>
        <li>Content on oriz that infringes your copyright (DMCA / Indian copyright complaints).</li>
        <li>Content that violates the IT Rules (defamation, obscenity, threats, impersonation).</li>
        <li>Privacy concerns under the DPDP Act 2023 — access, correction, deletion of your data.</li>
        <li>Account takeover or security incidents.</li>
      </ul>

      <p>
        Please include: a clear description of the issue, the URL(s) involved,
        proof you are the rights-holder (for copyright), and your contact
        details.
      </p>
    </article>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .officer {
    margin-block: 1.5rem;
    padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem;
    background: var(--paper-raised);
    border: 1px solid var(--rule);
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.875rem;
  }
  .officer p {
    margin: 0.4rem 0;
  }
  .officer strong {
    display: inline-block;
    min-width: 130px;
    color: var(--ink-mute);
    font-weight: 500;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    font-size: 0.75rem;
  }
</style>
